sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as MaaS Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS Terminate
    participant BBR as payload-processing (BBR)<br/>9004/TCP gRPC<br/>TLS SIMPLE
    participant Authorino as Authorino<br/>(AuthPolicy)
    participant MaaSAPI as maas-api<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS 1.2+
    participant Limitador as Limitador<br/>(TokenRateLimitPolicy)
    participant KServe as KServe Model<br/>HTTPS
    participant ExtLLM as External LLM Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PostgreSQL as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,ExtLLM: Flow 1: User Inference Request (API Key - Internal Model)

    Client->>Gateway: POST /{ns}/{model}/v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer sk-oai-*
    Gateway->>BBR: ext-proc filter (gRPC/9004)<br/>TLS SIMPLE
    BBR->>BBR: Extract model name from body<br/>Set X-Gateway-Model-Name header
    BBR-->>Gateway: Processed request
    Gateway->>Authorino: AuthPolicy evaluation
    Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/api-keys/validate<br/>TLS 1.2+ (NetworkPolicy)
    MaaSAPI->>PostgreSQL: Query API key (SHA-256 hash lookup)
    PostgreSQL-->>MaaSAPI: Key record + groups snapshot
    MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: 200 OK {valid, userId, groups}
    Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/subscriptions/select<br/>TLS 1.2+ (NetworkPolicy)
    MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: 200 OK {subscription, limits}
    Authorino-->>Gateway: Auth success + identity context
    Gateway->>Limitador: TokenRateLimitPolicy check<br/>(per userId + subscription)
    Limitador-->>Gateway: Rate limit OK
    Gateway->>KServe: Forward to InferenceService<br/>mTLS (stripped auth)
    KServe-->>Gateway: Inference response
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response

    Note over Client,ExtLLM: Flow 2: ExternalModel Routing

    Client->>Gateway: POST /{ns}/{model}/v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer token
    Gateway->>BBR: ext-proc filter (gRPC/9004)
    BBR->>K8sAPI: Read ExternalModel CR<br/>SA token
    K8sAPI-->>BBR: ExternalModel spec (provider endpoint)
    BBR->>K8sAPI: Read credentialRef Secret<br/>SA token
    K8sAPI-->>BBR: Provider API key
    BBR->>BBR: API format translation<br/>Inject provider credentials<br/>Strip user auth header
    BBR-->>Gateway: Transformed request
    Gateway->>Authorino: AuthPolicy evaluation
    Authorino-->>Gateway: Auth success
    Gateway->>Limitador: TokenRateLimitPolicy check
    Limitador-->>Gateway: Rate limit OK
    Gateway->>ExtLLM: Forward via ServiceEntry<br/>TLS SIMPLE (DestinationRule)<br/>Auth: Provider API key
    ExtLLM-->>Gateway: Provider response
    Gateway-->>Client: Translated response

    Note over Client,PostgreSQL: Flow 3: API Key Management

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/api-keys<br/>Auth: OpenShift token
    Gateway->>Authorino: AuthPolicy evaluation
    Authorino->>K8sAPI: TokenReview (validate OpenShift token)<br/>SA token
    K8sAPI-->>Authorino: Token valid {username, groups}
    Authorino-->>Gateway: Auth success + X-MaaS-Username/Group headers
    Gateway->>MaaSAPI: POST /v1/api-keys<br/>TLS 1.2+
    MaaSAPI->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(check model access)
    K8sAPI-->>MaaSAPI: Access granted
    MaaSAPI->>PostgreSQL: INSERT hashed key<br/>(sk-oai-{key_id}_{secret})
    PostgreSQL-->>MaaSAPI: Stored
    MaaSAPI-->>Gateway: 201 Created {plaintext key shown once}
    Gateway-->>Client: API Key response

    Note over Client,K8sAPI: Flow 4: Tenant Platform Reconciliation

    Note right of K8sAPI: maas-controller watches Tenant CR
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Tenant CR created/updated
    Note right of K8sAPI: Controller triggers reconciliation
    K8sAPI-->>K8sAPI: Kustomize render (embedded overlays)
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Post-render transforms<br/>(gateway config, OIDC, telemetry)
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Server-Side Apply<br/>(field manager: maas-controller)
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Check prerequisites<br/>(DB secret, Authorino CRDs, UWM)
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Wait for Deployments ready
    K8sAPI->>K8sAPI: Update Tenant status conditions
